SIGN 20 34
Volume I : Slayers Origins
Slayers was origionally
started in 2004 by the two top
generals of Slayers, Ice
and Relapse. 
In early 2004 there was a
large surge of "noob"clans
in which every new graalian
tried to make a clan.
These "noob" clans were
always growing due to two things: 
1) The new clans would
invite every person the
leaders saw. 
2) The surge of new clans
was supported by a surge
of new graalians. The new
graal members would join
eagerly hoping of being a
part of a higher cause. 
Ice saw the destructive
and degrading effect
of this eagerness and
quickly sought to end it.
Ice could tell that all
the "noob" clans were
destroying the
happiness of Graal and
so he attacked at their
heart. Ice ended a
few "noob" clans entirely
on his own through talk
and forcible persuasion.
Soon after Ice had
taken out a few clans, he
met Relapse. At first Ice
wasn't sure about
Relapse but he soon
found out that Relapse was
definitely someone to hang
on to. Relapse began
helping with the clan killing.
Many others joined in
with the clan killing,
but  most of them were
just the new Graalians
that were left hopeless
after the destruction of
their old clans. Ice and
Relapse quickly dispatched
of the noobs searching
for something to do,
and gained the support of
many stronger people.
The clan killings
continued until a good
balance had formed.
There were literally no
more "noob" clans.
SIGNEND
SIGN 28 34
Volume II: Slayers Begins
Everything was running
smoothly until a completely
new, unintelligent and
extrememly young noob,
named Darken, made a
guild called Dark Chaos.
Dark Chaos was a really
big problem. Since no
new "noob" clans had
been formed in a while,
there was a large surplus
of readily available new
Graalians that would be
happy to join any clan.
Dark Chaos grew rapidly
and became quickly known
for its "noob"ness and
complete idiocracy.
Many people gained the
compulsiveness to attack
any Dark Chaos members
in sight. In the mean time,
Ice and Relapse thought
they finally had time to
relax. It was much
different though. Many of
the followers of their cause
were restless and always
trying to find something
for them to do. The
followers were always
trying to tell Ice that
someone was starting a
clan or something to get
a fight going. Ice finally
put an end to that and
said that clan slaying was
finally over for the time being
When Ice heard some
hype about Dark Chaos, he
took no interest due to the
normal interests of the
people following him. It
wasn't until he found out
that his friend Relapse
had actually taken his own
stand against Dark Chaos
that he gave any care.
Relapse asked Ice for help
defeating Dark Chaos.
Relapse had rallied the
few good and respectable
followers of the clan killers
and set up a resistance.
Relapse didn't have much
structure to his new
followers and got Ice's help.
The only real threat to his
success was Dark Chaos.
He privately asked Ice to
disguise himself and
infiltrate Dark Chaos and
to kill it from the inside. Ice
agreed. To the quick
satisfaction of Relapse,
Ice had disguised himself
and gained a leadership
role straight from the start.
It was a complicated matter
of the main war and
Relapse and Ice's quiet
war. Relapse led the main
attack and slowly destroyed
the morale of the young
Graalians while Ice had
them kicked out or made
them quit. By the time Ice
had intervened, Dark
Chaos had about 40 - 50
members, which is a
massive amount for any
Graal guild today. Most
members didn't give it
all their heart and were
easy to get to quit. Others
had to be kicked with odd
excuses Ice would
persuade were right to
Darken. By the time Ice
handed over the remnants
of the war to Relapse, two
clans had been killed, Dark
Chaos had 3 or 4 members,
and the trial clan Slayers
had been established.
SIGNEND
SIGN 35 34
Volume III: Slayers
Initial Troubles
Ice dissapproved of
Slayers greatly due to the
whole point of the clan
killing was to stop trial
clans that weren't good.
But Ice helped his friend
Relapse out anyways, and
had helped prove that
Slayers was able to stand
up for itself. Slayers was a
formiddable clan. Due to
all the hype Ice had
created on clan killing
Relapse took the guild to
many heights and
selectively recruited
which was the first to
selectively recruit in a
long time. Relapse chose
only the best he could
get, and it worked.
Relapse on his own, with
the help of the guild
killed a few more noob
clans that popped up. He
added to the clan kill
toll to a toppling 17
"noob" clans and 2 real
ones. Among these clans
were: Dark Chaos, Dark
Mages, Zelda Angels, and
Hyrule Royal Family(realguild). 
Shortly after the creation
of Slayers, Ice
disappeared. Ice wouldn't
come back for over 6
months and then only on
and off for a very short
amount of time. Relapse
also left for a long
amount of time after the
guild became structurely
sound. When Ice returned,
Relapse was gone and
Slayers had seemingly
disappeared. Ice left
again for a longer amount
of time. Fortunately
Relapse returned and had
noticed Slayers new
success, they instantly
became reinvolved with
the guild.
Both took the role of
leading generals in the
guild, so as not to
disturb the leadership at
the time. But who were
these new leaders?
SIGNEND
