SIGN 43 34
Volume IV: Slayers Seed to
Greatness
In the absence of their
leader Relapse, the prime
young adventurers,
DarkHunter and Death, took
over the guild. A good
friend to Relapse and Ice,
Zero helped build the
guild up again. Zero,
DarkHunter, and Death all
lead the guild back into
prosperity. Destroying all
foes and defying the
unlikelyness that they
would be killed, the 3
leaders held the guild
together. Eventually Zero
left the guild to
DarkHunter and Death who
held things together quite
nicely.
DarkHunter and Death were
good friends with good
ideas who had a great
impact on the guild. The
guild had its rough times
 but DarkHunter and Death
stuck together to create.
After the return of Ice
and Relapse, DarkHunter
and Death faced a slight
bit of shakiness due to a
little bit of the older
members intervention.
Eventually it led to a
small amount of bickering
in between the four.
This arguing nearly made
Relapse quit and try to
end Slayers, but Ice and
DarkHunter helped quiet
the situation down.
Shortly after that clash
of leadership, DarkHunter
and Death had at it and
ultimately got Death to
quit. In Death's absence,
DarkHunter took over with
full leadership and
decided to create a new
family. His new family was the
Katana family. The
name Katana represented
sharp and quick
decisiveness.
Death settled down after
a bit of exile and
rejoined the guild with
DarkHunter's acceptance.
After apologizing to
DarkHunter, Death became
leader again. Once Death
returned as a leader he
compromised with Dark and
restructered the guild.
Although the guild became
shaky after the
reconstruction of the
guild, it worked very
efficiently. The guild
instantly began to grow
and become known in Graal.
Death's new policies
helped strengthen the
guild. Fortunately at the
time of reconstruction,
the guild was not
threatened in anyway. The
guild is currently in the
hands of DarkHunter, Death
and a new, encouraging
member Mighty Thor.
From here on out, we can
only imagine what will
happen with Slayers.
Long live Slayers!
SIGNEND
