SIGN 42 40
March 3, 2004
Today I have finally
decided how i would like
to take on the problem of
these noob clans. It seems
to me that the best plan
of approach is to just
flat out destroy them. If
there was less of these
new people, then we
wouldn't have this
problem. I think I will go
after the Sith clan
tomorrow.

March 15, 2004
I have killed 2 more
clans. These clans were
just as easy to destroy as
the first. What really
frustrated me was that I
found new people from the
Sith clan in these clans.
Fortunately, deciding to
be covert in my operations
allowed me to dissuade
them from joining other
clans. I also met an
especially talented new
person today. His name is
Relapse.


March 17, 2004
There is nothing special
about the past few days
except for the
eccentricity and talent of
Relapse. I have decided to
let him continue to follow
me. I think he enjoys the
fact that I send so many
others away and let him
stay. Whether he does or
doesn't, he is a welcoming
relief, showing that not
all of the new people are
going to be annoying.
March 19, 2004
Relapse has shown his
prowess again. He has helped
me destroy another clan. It
was surprisingly easier using
a tactic we thought up
yesterday. He is strong
enough to defeat most of the
clan members of these noob
clans. This way he destroys
morale while I convince its
members to leave. He also
allowed for me to talk to the
leaders by continually
attacking them while I talked to
them. He has much talent and
is very useful. I think I will keep
him.
April 1, 2004
Today was an awesome day!
We killed 2 clans today
and did so with such
efficiency. The clans
didn't know what hit them!
Relapse decided to play a
joke for April Fool's Day.
He faked like he was
defecting to make a noob
clan. It really got me.
Relapse has become a
friend now. I don't think
I see him so much as my
subordinate anymore.
June 2, 2004
I think I'll call it a
retirement. I'm done with
clan killing. No new
clans. I'm pretty sure we
stopped them for a while.
I've notified many of the
followers that we are done
for now.
June 13, 2004
A new clan has formed. I
ignored the initial
threats that I heard from
the followers, but now I
have seen them all over
the place. I'm not sure
what to do. I'm not even
quite sure why our
followers still give me
info.

June 21, 2004
Dark Chaos continues to
grow. I said I was
retiring from clan killing
but this is getting out of
hand. These guys in Dark
Chaos are obviously
morons. Relapse asked me
to help him today. I'm not
sure what to do. He
obviously chose his forces
well, but he gave the
group a name: Slayers. I'm
sure he has already had
the intentions of making
it a clan killing clan. I
despise the idea but
Relapse has become such a
good friend. I'm not sure
what to do.

I've reached the last page in
this book, i think i will start
another one.
SIGNEND
SIGN 44 40
June 29, 2004
Emperor Darken is the
leader of Dark Chaos, and
after only 5 days of
trying my new technique, I
have become a leader in
the clan. I have been
given the rank of General
which is basically right
hand to Darken. There is a
co-leader, but I'm sure
I'll find a way to dispose
of him. I have presented
my what is going on in
Dark Chaos.
July 7, 2004
After having such a high
impact on Dark Chaos, I
could easily remove
members. The guild was
almost up to 60 members
when I finally had this
opportunity. The clan's
member count is quickly
dropping. To my dismay,
the members are defecting
to a new clan: The Dark
Magus. It's a very cult-like
clan. The worst part is that it
is led by the previous
co-leader of Dark Chaos.


July 10, 2004
Relapse is weeding out the
weak links in Slayers and
is effectively reducing
Dark Chaos' chance at
survival. Relapse has
avoided a dual war with
Dark Magus and has helped
me talk with the leader.
Although the leader hates
us, I think I can smell
the eminence of his
defeat. He is realizing
that the members he is
recieving are only the
weak links in Dark Chaos.
He thinks my only
intentions are to help
him, and he is warming up
to me. He still thinks I'm
trying to save Dark Chaos.
July 19, 2004
Dark Mages is over. The
leader quit and disbanded
the guild. The leader also
realized he had ruined his
reputation, so he took on
the new name of GodSyde.
Now I can take down
Darken.
July 23, 2004
He refuses to quit. He
knows my intentions now.
He has used my coming
clean to recruit back old
members. Similarly I have
used the excuse that the
guild was so weak I
infiltrated it to lose the
previous members. Darken
has no power anymore.
Everyone hates Darken and
Dark Chaos, but he refuses
to quit. Relapse and I are
now going to try the all
out punish move on Darken.


July 24, 2004
It's worked! We lamed the
fool from dawn until dusk!
He finally declared the
end of Dark Chaos! Relapse
has sent one of his
Slayers to stalk Darken to
make sure no plans are
made. It was spectacular!
I didn't think it would
work but the Slayers
defended off the last
followers of Darken's noob
clan, and provided a way
for me and Relapse to
force Darken into
submission. Although I
don't fully approve of
Slayers, they are
wonderful! There are
actually people LOOKING to
join Slayers. They have
some deep respect, no
matter how shaky it is.
DARK CHAOS IS OVER!


July 30, 2004
Relapse has everything
under control. Slayers has
a few members, all of
which are the best men
Relapse could find. With
my advice, Relapse has
chosen very selectively on
his members. I'm declaring
my new retirement now that
there is a great clan with
experience on how to
destroy clans. I can
finally relax. I think I
will take some time to
leave Graal and explore on
my own. Relapse can handle
everything for now. I'll
make sure I take some time
to speak to all of my
friends before I leave.
Talking to Zero and Clel
will be a welcoming relief
since I haven't talked to
them in weeks.


February 16, 2005
It is nearing winter. I
have finally returned. I
have seen Slayers almost
no where in sight. After a
long amount of searching I
cannot find Relapse. It
took a while but I found
out that he had followed
my example and left too,
in order to enlighten
himself as I had. Slayers
must have died off. It
wasn't until earlier today
that I noticed someone
from the Slayers who said
they were still around
sometimes. I have decided
to go out again now that I
have returned to visit,
with no one to return to.
July 27, 2006
I have returned and left
Graal more than once
before this date, but
never found the time to
write in this journal. It
is now important for me to
tell that Slayers has
become a real formiddable
clan. Apparently the two
young prospects who are in
control of the guild now,
reconstructed the clan.
Slayers has become a
dominant force in everyday
life. I have found Relapse
too. Relapse was no longer
the leader's, and so I
have requested that also.
DarkHunter and Death are
very good with the guild.
Relapse approves of them
and we all enjoy a bond of
friendship in between us.
For the good old days, we
killed a clan called XDF.
It was extremely fun and
really easy with the new
highly developed slayers.
Relapse and I played a
dominant role in the
destruction. As for now, I
believe I will put this
journal away. I see no
more need to use it. Life
has become peaceful.....
